.TH LPF-TEST 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.2.1" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-test \- run policy assertion fixtures
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf test <fixture>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Run policy assertions covering decisions, NAT, route, queue, log, and tables.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-junit <path>
write JUnit\-compatible test output
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf test fixtures/tests/basic.yaml
.SH FILES
lpf\-policy\-tests(5)
.SH SAFETY NOTES
Policy tests must run before guarded apply in CI workflows.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-explain(8), lpf\-policy\-tests(5)
